# PR Management Agent

A lightweight AI-style Purchase Requisition (PR) Management system built using Python.

This project demonstrates:
- Intent-based routing
- Tool calling architecture
- PR listing with pagination
- PR cart management
- LangChain-style agent prompting

---

# Features

- Show active PRs
- Paginate PR results
- Add PRs to cart
- Update PR cart quantity
- Simple supervisor routing system
- LangChain agent prompt integration

---

# Project Structure

```bash
.
├── app.py
├── orchestrator.py
├── pr_management_tools.py
└── agents/
    └── pr_management_agent.py
```

---

# How It Works

## 1. Supervisor Router (`orchestrator.py`)

The supervisor router analyzes user input and routes requests to the correct tool.

Supported intents:

| User Intent | Tool Called |
|---|---|
| Show PRs | `get_pr_list_tool()` |
| View More PRs | `paginate_pr_tool()` |
| Add PR to Cart | `add_pr_to_cart_tool()` |
| Update Quantity | `update_pr_cart_qty_tool()` |

---

## 2. PR Tools (`pr_management_tools.py`)

Contains:
- Mock PR database
- Pagination logic
- Cart management
- Quantity update logic

### Available Tools

```python
get_pr_list_tool()
paginate_pr_tool()
add_pr_to_cart_tool(uuid, qty)
update_pr_cart_qty_tool(uuid, qty)
```

---

## 3. PR Management Agent (`pr_management_agent.py`)

Defines the AI agent behavior using a LangChain prompt template.

The agent:
- Understands PR-related tasks
- Restricts unsupported actions
- Returns raw tool outputs

---

## 4. CLI App (`app.py`)

Simple terminal-based interaction loop.

Runs the supervisor router continuously until the user exits.

---

# Installation

## Clone Repository

```bash
git clone <your-repo-url>
cd <repo-name>
```

## Install Dependencies

```bash
pip install langchain-core
```

---

# Run Application

```bash
python app.py
```

---

# Example Usage

## Show PRs

```bash
User: show my pr
```

---

## View More PRs

```bash
User: next
```

---

## Add PR to Cart

```bash
User: add pr 1a2b3c01-0001-4a0c-b0db-111111111111 qty 5
```

---

## Update PR Quantity

```bash
User: update pr 1a2b3c01-0001-4a0c-b0db-111111111111 qty 10
```

---

# Sample PR Object

```python
{
    "uuid": "1a2b3c01-0001-4a0c-b0db-111111111111",
    "pr_name": "LAPTOPS - VARIANT 1 - BLACK",
    "qty": 60,
    "location": "Pune"
}
```

---

# Current Limitations

- In-memory storage only
- No database integration
- No authentication
- Basic string parsing
- No persistent sessions

---

